sdf:title: Muscle Oxygen Saturation
sdf:copyright: Copyright 2019 Open Connectivity Foundation, Inc. All rights reserved.
description: This Resource describes the muscle oxygen saturation (SmO2), which is the percentage of hemoglobin that is saturated with oxygen in the capillaries of a muscle. The unit is percentage. The smo2 Property is a read-only value that is provided by the server.
